    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An alphabet created by the scholar Mesrop Mashtots ca. 405 CE, with 36 original characters, and auxiliary letters added later historically. Used from the fifth century for the preservation of Armenian cultural and literary identity.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
